The paper deals with link prediction in social networks using matrix factorization and completion techniques. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the specific characteristics of social networks, such as their degree distributions, which are relevant to the field of social network analysis, covered by cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper uses convex optimization techniques, which are relevant to the field of optimization and control, covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Systems and Control).
